            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41980",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hujuice",
                        "name": "hujuice",
                        "displayName": "Sergio Vaccaro",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is because an (odd?) Apache (2.x?) behavior.\r\nHere is the reason and the solution: http:\/\/httpd.apache.org\/docs\/2.2\/mod\/core.html#allowencodedslashes\r\n\r\nSetting\r\n{code}AllowEncodedSlashes On{code}\r\nin the Apache configuration is a solution. Be careful because this directive must be given in server config or virtual host context.\r\n\r\nIf this is considered a good solution, this bug could be a documentation lack.\r\n\r\nSee also this post: http:\/\/zend-framework-community.634137.n4.nabble.com\/Re-Parameter-values-with-slashes-td653237.html\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hujuice",
                        "name": "hujuice",
                        "displayName": "Sergio Vaccaro",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-08-14T04:47:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-08-14T04:47:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48466",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=max4ever",
                        "name": "max4ever",
                        "displayName": "Maxim Postoronca",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "if i use {code}$this->url(array('module' => $module,'controller'=>'widget', 'action'=>'abc','ditta_id'=> $ditta['id'], 'url' => '\/ordine\/index')), null, TRUE);{code} \r\n it doesn't work\r\n\r\nif i use {code}$this->url(array('module' => $module,'controller'=>'widget', 'action'=>'abc','ditta_id'=> $ditta['id'], 'url' => urlencode('\/ordine\/index') ), null, TRUE);{code} \r\nit works, but i have then to {code} urldecode() {code}  the 'url' parameter",
